In a statement given at Cross Hall, President Biden announced that Israel and Hamas have agreed to a mutual, unconditional ceasefire. He commended Prime Minister Netanyahu for his decision to end the conflict and expressed full support for Israel's right to defend itself against rocket attacks. President Biden also thanked Egypt and other Middle Eastern countries for their diplomatic efforts to bring about the ceasefire. He expressed condolences for the civilian casualties on both sides and pledged to work with the United Nations and international stakeholders to provide humanitarian assistance and support reconstruction efforts in Gaza. President Biden emphasized the importance of working with the Palestinian Authority, not Hamas, to ensure the security of both Israelis and Palestinians. He expressed optimism for progress and committed to continuing diplomatic efforts towards a peaceful resolution.